# Copy to `.env.local` and restart `npm run dev`.
# Use the SAME Aptos devnet fullnode URL as Nightly (network / custom RPC), where applicable.
# Include the /v1 suffix (the example app will append /v1 if you forget).

# Public devnet (default in README / explorer; recommended for the published demo module)
VITE_APTOS_FULLNODE_URL=https://api.devnet.aptoslabs.com/v1

# Optional: Geomi / Aptos Labs API key for higher rate limits on the Node API (Authorization: Bearer).
# Create a key at https://geomi.dev — use a Frontend Key for browser apps (VITE_ exposes this to clients).
# VITE_APTOS_API_KEY=

# Alternative public fullnode host (same chain as above)
# VITE_APTOS_FULLNODE_URL=https://fullnode.devnet.aptoslabs.com/v1

# Staging devnet — different chain from public devnet; can 502 / rate-limit more often
# VITE_APTOS_FULLNODE_URL=https://api.devnet.staging.aptoslabs.com/v1

# If the browser console shows "not valid JSON", "Bad Gateway", or "Per anonymous…":
# the RPC returned HTML/text instead of JSON — wrong URL, outage, or rate limit.
# Switch hosts above, wait a minute, and match your wallet’s Devnet Custom RPC exactly.
#
# Petra “Simulation error” HTTP 429 + Geomi “compute units” / staging URL: your *wallet* may still use
# api.devnet.staging.aptoslabs.com — change Petra’s Custom RPC to the same host as above, or raise limits in Geomi.
# https://geomi.dev/docs/faq

# VITE_SIGIL_MODULE_ADDRESS=0x...
